review_blob: Poured a light hazy color.  Lemony tasting, but much too thin for my liking.  Glad I only bought one bottle.
Poured a very nice color.  Probably the best brown ale Ive ever tried.
Bottle.  Nice color, small head.  Interesting use of a fruit that is seldom used in beer.  Not overpowering... good brew.
Well-hopped brew.  Nice color.  One of the better offerings Ive tried from Shiner.
Just tried this one for the first time... quite possibly the best tasting beer that Ive ever tried.  A crazy blend of sour, sweet, and fruit tasting.  Go out of your way for this one!
Poured from a bottle.  Traditional brown ale with strong banana aroma.  Pleasant aftertaste.  Would drink another.
On tap at Liuzzas in NOLA.  A good summer wheat beer with a strong, but not overpowering strawberry taste.  Very refreshing beer!

beer_brewer_name: Vermont Hard Cider Company, LLC (C&C; Group)
review_blob: Not much like a typical beer, but very refreshing.  Not overly sweet.  Pretty good stuff!
Pours a nice amber color.  Reminds me of some of the brown ales Ive tried.  Somewhat bitter.  Good beer.
Bottle.  Thin head.  Ample hops in the aroma and taste.  Glad I get to add a beer from France to my list.  Pretty good lager.
Drank one at a baseball game.  I had a difficult time finishing it.  Bland, watered down, nothing appealing about it.
Bottle.  Solid all-around Hefe.  Aroma of banana, and a bit of a citrus taste as well.  Pours a nice hazy color with a thin head.  Would drink another!  Great label too.
Poured from a bottle.  Im not too fond of the fruit beer style, but this one was decent enough.  A bit too watery... could have been stronger on both the "beer" taste and raspberry taste.

Poured a nice amber color.  Not much head.  Nice mixture of malt and hops.
Wish I had more than one to drink.  Excellent lager.
Poured from a bottle.  Not much head.  Somewhat cloudy and light appearance.  More citrus flavor than other Belgian Whites that I have tried.  Pretty good beer when Hoegaarden is not available.
Bottle.  Poured golden color with a nice white head.  Aroma of banana.   A fine example of why Hefe-Weizens are some of my favorite beers.
Poured from a bottle.  Pretty good German Pilsener.  Enough bitter hops to make this one interesting.
Bottle.  Compares favorably to other Brown Ales Ive tried.  Not as much of a pecan flavor as I expected, but definitely made for a good tasting beer.  Not overly sweet; just right.

Ive tried over 50 unique beers now, and I keep coming back to this one as one of my favorites.  Nice golden color, light bodied, good tasting, though perhaps not as complex as the Hefe-Weizen from Franziskaner.
UPDATED: MAR 23, 2010
Bottle.  Pours a nice golden color.  A steady stream of bubbles, like champagne.  A strong beer, a Belgian classic.
Bottle.  This was my first taste of a Schwarzbier.  Poured a rich black color with tan head.  Definite tastes of coffee/chocolate.  Would drink another.
Bottle.  German brews are some of my favorites.  This dark wheat beer has a very smooth malt aroma, nice chocolate color, and good mouth feel.  I recommend this one!
